news.title: KK Rajeev Nambiar resigns as CEO of Shree Digvijay Cement Company
news.para: The board also approved appointment of Ramanujan Krishnakumar, currently working as senior vice president (Manufacturing), as an additional director, CEO & MD of Shree Digvijay Cement Company.

news.title: CPI Property Group commences internal audit after short-seller report
news.para: Short-selling hedge fund Muddy Waters last week disclosed its bet against the credit of CPI Property Group sending a key bond of the company to fall by the most on record.

news.title: Aldar Properties completes $291 million acquisition of London Square
news.para: "Aldar intends to leverage its expertise and balance sheet to support London Square's land acquisition strategy to enable it to develop larger and prime central London sites," the two companies said in a joint statement on Friday.

news.title: Surya Roshni's CEO of steel operations resigns
news.para: "Tarun Baldua was on extension post-completion of his superannuation age. He is being relieved with immediate effect," Surya Roshni said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: Two commercial complexes in Vadodara sealed for fire safety violation
news.para: The department has been taking up extensive sealing drives after issuing a series of notices to commercial complexes in the city. On Tuesday it sealed the two commercial properties as a part of the drive.

news.title: AltF Coworking plans to open over 20 co-working centers by FY25
news.para: AltF Coworking is looking to raise funds at an estimated figure of $1-2 million in Q1 2024 in order to fund the acquisition of 4-6 properties in the following financial year.

news.title: Greater Noida: Eight stations to come up on Aqua Line's sector 142-Botanical Garden leg
news.para: The Delhi Metro Rail Corporation (DMRC) has revised its project report for the 11.56-km-long corridor to add new stations near the Noida Authority’s upcoming office in Sector 96, Sectors 44, 105 and 93 on an elevated corridor parallel to the expressway.

news.title: Mumbai: Over 24 lakh collected in fines from 'polluting' construction sites
news.para: The highest fine collection — Rs 12.6 lakh — was from construction sites that failed to keep the surroundings clean and allowed accumulation of dust and debris, followed by Rs 9.2 lakh on those involved in illegal construction and demolition waste.

news.title: The Phoenix Mills' subsidiaries receives order for GST demand & penalty
news.para: While MCRPL received notice of Rs 97.63 lakh (including interest and penalty), PHLL received notice of Rs 6.15 crore. The notices have been served over the GST liability on account of claiming of Block ITC as per section 17(5) of MGST Act.

news.title: Gap Associates, SUN Realty Partnership & BMS Projects' JV buys 42,241 sq meters land in Dholera SIR
news.para: Base price of the land auction was approximately Rs 17.42 crore (Rs 4,125 per sq meters). Maximum permissible FSI is 5 on this plot as per the GDCR of Dholera SIR.

news.title: HC contempt notice to Madhya Pradesh housing board principal secretary
news.para: ​Justice Subodh Abhyankar in an order dated November 29 noted, “In the considered opinion of this court, the manner in which principal secretary Neeraj Mandloi has conducted himself clearly falls within the purview of contempt of court.”

news.title: Maharashtra: Stamp duty deficit in 2.3 lakh cases, amnesty plan to help
news.para: The department had identified the defaulters during an audit. The official said the amnesty scheme, which would provide an exemption in stamp duty and penalty, was announced at the state cabinet meeting on Wednesday.

news.title: Land audit of Greater Noida villages soon
news.para: The authority has started the process of hiring binding a consultant agency for conducting the land audit and door to door survey.

news.title: Gujarat government to lose 18% GST in sale of eight plots in Ahmedabad
news.para: Sources said, according to the corporation’s recently revised leasing policy, these plots will be sold on sales deeds and not leased on 99-year period.

news.title: Property registration in Mumbai municipal area rises 8% in November 2023
news.para: In November last year, as many as 8,965 units were registered. The registration number is higher year-on-year, but it is less than in October when 10,607 units were registered.

news.title: China Evergrande seeks to avoid liquidation with last-ditch debt plan: Sources
news.para: China Evergrande has until a Hong Kong court hearing on Monday to present a "concrete" revised debt restructuring proposal for offshore creditors, a judge said last month after its original plan had lapsed.

news.title: Registration begins for penthouses, super HIG flats offered by DDA
news.para: ​The DDA has announced starting of the registration process through an e-brochure. These flats will be offered through e-auction mode for which the registration began on Thursday, they said.

news.title: Unitech CMD's tenure extended by two years till January 2026
news.para: ​In a regulatory filing on Thursday, Unitech informed that the Ministry of Corporate Affairs (MCA) has extended the tenure of Yudhvir Singh Malik (IAS Retd), as Chairman and Managing Director of the company for a further period of two years, which is from January 21, 2024, to January 20, 2026.

news.title: Kolkata civic body waives prior sanction need for building plans on plots up to 5,000 sq ft
news.para: According to a modified KMC building rule, owners of plots within the defined size wishing to construct a building need to engage an architect or an LBS and apply for a plan sanction online.
